{
  "texts": [
    "However, across architectures this is not the case.",
    "For example, Adam provides a computational efficiency gain for transformers, yet most state-of-the-art LSTMs relied on RMSProp or plain SGD over Adam [Merity et al., 2017, Melis et al., 2017, Keskar and Socher, 2017].",
    "To help identify these interactions, we train a transformer model similar to the original architecture developed by Vaswani et al. [2017].",
    "In this \"Retro\" Transformer, four algorithmic improvements are reverted.",
    "We switch from SwiGLU to GeLU, pre-RMSNorm to post-layernorm, rotary encoding to sinusoidal encodings, and cosine decay learning rate schedule to square root decay schedule."
  ]
}